<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="_29nNkNnmEdmO6L4XMImrsA" name="conduct_review_meeting,{01C0BC09-C421-438A-B4C4-351C46A244C9}" guid="_29nNkNnmEdmO6L4XMImrsA" changeDate="2011-03-26T16:27:52.280-0600" version="7.1.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    In a review, the&amp;nbsp;moderator sets an agenda and as the review proceeds reviewers bring up issues as they are&#xD;
    encountered.&amp;nbsp; The recorder records issues and then adds them to the issue list and modifies the agenda.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    In an offline review, the moderator sets an agenda for the reviewers.&amp;nbsp; The responsible role reviews any comments&#xD;
    made by the reviewers and provides any needed responses.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    In a walkthrough, the responsible role presents the material to be reviewed, while the recorder summarizes decisions,&#xD;
    actions, and key discussion points. This review can cover lots of material and many people may attend and not be as&#xD;
    prepared as the other types of reviews.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    In a peer review, ensure that the exit criteria for the peer review are satisfied.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    In an inspection, the responsible lists one or two aspects to be inspected, while the recorder summarizes decisions,&#xD;
    actions and key discussion points.&amp;nbsp; This is a rapid evaluation of materials.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></mainDescription>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    To facilitate the review so as to maximize the productivity of the reviewers and meet defined quality requirements.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
